#: ../../../installing_prerequisites.rst:-1
msgid ""
"Find instructions on how to install the necessary prerequisites for Spack on "
"various operating systems, including Linux and macOS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing_prerequisites.rst:13
msgid "Spack Prerequisites"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing_prerequisites.rst:15
msgid ""
"Spack relies on a few basic utilities to be present on the system where it "
"runs, depending on the operating system. To install them, follow the "
"instructions below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing_prerequisites.rst:19
msgid "Linux"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing_prerequisites.rst:21
msgid "For **Debian** and **Ubuntu** users:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing_prerequisites.rst:23
msgid ""
"$ apt update\n"
"$ apt install file bzip2 ca-certificates g++ gcc gfortran git gzip lsb-"
"release patch python3 tar unzip xz-utils zstd"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing_prerequisites.rst:28
msgid "For **RHEL**, **AlmaLinux**, and **Rocky Linux** users:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing_prerequisites.rst:30
msgid ""
"$ dnf install epel-release\n"
"$ dnf install file bzip2 ca-certificates git gzip patch python3 tar unzip xz "
"zstd gcc gcc-c++ gcc-gfortran"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing_prerequisites.rst:36
msgid "macOS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing_prerequisites.rst:38
msgid ""
"On macOS, the Command Line Tools package is required, and the full Xcode "
"suite may be necessary for some packages, such as Qt and apple-gl. To "
"install Xcode, you can use the following command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing_prerequisites.rst:41
msgid "$ xcode-select --install"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing_prerequisites.rst:45
msgid ""
"For most packages, the Xcode command-line tools are sufficient. However, "
"some packages like ``qt`` require the full Xcode suite. You can check to see "
"which you have installed by running:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing_prerequisites.rst:49
msgid "$ xcode-select -p"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing_prerequisites.rst:53
msgid "If the output is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing_prerequisites.rst:55
msgid "/Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Developer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing_prerequisites.rst:59
msgid "you already have the full Xcode suite installed. If the output is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing_prerequisites.rst:62
msgid "/Library/Developer/CommandLineTools"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing_prerequisites.rst:66
msgid ""
"you only have the command-line tools installed. The full Xcode suite can be "
"installed through the App Store. Make sure to launch the Xcode application "
"and accept the license agreement before using Spack. It may ask you to "
"install additional components. Alternatively, the Xcode license can be "
"accepted through the command line:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing_prerequisites.rst:72
msgid "$ sudo xcodebuild -license accept"
msgstr ""
